content.description: Start on slab to steep fun runnel.
content.location: To the right of Super Cross

content.description: On the far left (west) side of the crag. Ascend the left-most route, just right of the arete. Climb past 3 bolts on amazing knobby granite, in addition using slings for knobs. Bolted anchors with chains.
content.location: On the far left (west) side of the crag. Ascend the left-most route, just right of the arete.

content.description: A “fun” off-width, with easy face to bolted chain anchors on top.
content.protection: Cams to 3”, with one nut to do the “Thread through” at the top of the chimney (top down).
content.location: Left around corner from Separation Anxiety.

content.description: An interesting start leads to technical face climbing. The upper section is easy knob pulling.
content.protection: 6 bolts, knob slings and some very small nuts to protect the small crack between bolts 2 and 3.

content.description: Starts in the low angle wide crack, you can protect it with small gear and a judicious use of slings. Lots of slings. The route then bends up the steep face around the corner, and maybe with enough slings it won’t catch the corner and create heinous rope drag. Climb a hell of a long way up a knobby slab using slings to a two bolt anchor. Walk off.
content.protection: Gear to 6” in the book, but could most likely use singles to 2”, 4 bolts. MANY slings
content.location: Left of the roof from the steep stuff, starts in the low angle wide crack.

content.description: A steep jug haul. If you're not used to steep climbs, this will feel harder. The climb "Yain't" to the right is also rad (.10a).
content.protection: 5 bolts plus the usual thin slings for knobs, and some gear up to 2". No need for a big rack. One cam each will suffice. Chain anchor.
content.location: On the main face, this route goes up a black runnel to the right of the roof. "Yain't" is the left black streak (.10a) and Holeshot is the right black streak. You only go over a bit of the roof, more like a bulge. Optional gear down low.

content.description: Fun plates, similar to Separation Anxiety. Well protected.
content.location: Starts on far right side of sloping ledge. Shares same anchor as SA.
